Moving Average models for Distance¶

In [41]:
### Calculating moving average of distance by models such as Simple moving average, Cumulative moving average and
### Exponential Moving average
Travel['SMA_Distance'] = Travel['Distance'].rolling(window=3).mean()
Travel['CMA_Distance'] = Travel['Distance'].expanding().mean()
Travel['EMA_Distance'] = Travel['Distance'].ewm(span=3,adjust=False).mean()
In [58]:
### ploting Simple moving average of distance in graph
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(Travel['Date'], Travel['Distance'], label='Actual')
plt.plot(Travel['Date'], Travel['SMA_Distance'], label='SMA')
plt.title('Simple Average Models for Distance')
plt.legend()

### calculating Simple, Cumulative and Exponential moving average of AvgSpeed from the Travel Dataset

### Using Timeseries Model for prediction of distance travelled in given date
ts_distance = Travel[['Date', 'Distance']].set_index('Date')
model_distance = ARIMA(ts_distance, order=(1, 0, 0))
model_fit_distance = model_distance.fit()
pred_distance = model_fit_distance.predict(start_date='01-02-2012', end_date='28-02-2012')
